definitions.definition: A town in Ellesmere Urban parish, north Shropshire , England ( OS grid ref SJ3934 ) .
A rural locality in South Burnett Region, Queensland , Australia .
A lagoon in Canterbury , New Zealand ; in full, Lake Ellesmere .
A rural locality in Selwyn district, Canterbury , New Zealand , north-west of Lake Ellesmere.
The Earl of Ellesmere , a title in the British peerage, named after Ellesmere, Shropshire.
